# Objective

Build a Playwright-based automation agent using TypeScript that can:

- Collect and analyze web data
- Validate UI and API behavior
- Generate structured outputs (logs, reports, drafts)
- Support scalable QA and automation workflows

# Approach

Use a simple modular structure:

1. Data collection (Playwright)
2. Parsing and normalization
3. Validation (UI and API)
4. Output generation
5. Reporting and logging

# Architecture

[Collector] → [Parser] → [Validator] → [Generator] → [Reporter]

# Project Structure

src/
  collectors/
  parsers/
  validators/
  services/
  workflows/
  utils/

data/
reports/
tests/
config/

# Rules

- Use TypeScript only
- Use Playwright for browser automation
- Use Page Object Model where appropriate
- Prefer `data-testid` selectors
- Never use `waitForTimeout`
- Use Playwright auto-waiting
- Generate reusable, modular code
- Save reports into `/reports`
- Add logging and error handling to every workflow
- Keep tests independent and parallel-safe